GAZETTE NOTICE NO. 3328

THE PHYSICAL AND LAND USE PLANNING ACT ( Cap. 303)

COUNTY GOVERNMENT OF NAROK MUNICIPALITY OF KILGORIS

INTENTION TO PREPARE A LOCAL PHYSICAL AND LAND USE DEVELOPMENT PLAN

Title of Development Plan: Maji Moto Market Centre Local Physical and Land Use Development Plan, Plan No. R1924/2026/01

PURSUANT to the provisions of section (47) of the Physical and Land Use Planning Act and other relevant legislations and regulations, notice  is  given  that  the  County  Government  of  Narok  intends  to commence preparation of the above plan on the 6th February, 2026.

The purpose of the plan is to provide an overall spatial framework to  guide  the  sustainable  growth  and  development  of  the  area  within Maji Moto Market Centre in Narok South Sub-county.

The objectives of the plan are:

(a) To  provide  a  forum  for  stakeholder  participation  in  plan preparation and implementation;

(b) To define a vision for future growth and development of the Market Centre over the next 10-15 years;

(c) To provide a basis for survey and regularization of plots and public utilities;

(d) Provide  and  coordinate  through  a  spatial  framework  the development of infrastructural facilities and services;

(e) Provide a framework for settlement development by suggesting appropriate land use densities, and activity guidelines;

(f) To provide the basis for development control through preparation  of  zoning  plans,  action  area  plans  and  land  use regulations;

(g) Identifying environmentally fragile areas and suggesting measures to ensure their protection;

(h) To provide a basis for co-ordinated programming of projects and budget;

(i) Provide  a  framework  to  unlock  the  real  socio-economic potential  of  this  Market  Centre  by  suggesting  measures  to deal  with  underlying  problems  and  for  the  exploitation  of existing opportunities.

Any written comments on the proposed plan may be addressed or delivered to the office of the County Executive Committee Member; Lands, Housing, Physical Planning and Urban Development, P.O. Box 898-20500, Narok Town (Municipality Office) or Ward Administrator, Naroosura Ward, (Naroosura Market Centre) during the normal  working  hours  or  through  E-mail-lands@narok.go.ke  within twenty one (21) days from the date of publication of this notice.

Dated the 6th February, 2026.

ANTHONY S. NAMUNKUK,

CECM, Lands, Housing, Physical Planning and Urban Development.

MR/811099
